               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182804100087"></xptr>RICHARD HARLING. I was coming out of Lambs'-buildings; Barnes called to me, "Dick, stop that man," I said, "Hallo my friend, what are you at;" he threw he plank down at my feet; he ran, and was taken by Barnes.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was very much in distress.</p>


